==Slovak==
===Etymology===
:The middle section of Latin '''[[confirmatio]]''', or '''firm''', assimilated into '''birm''' + '''-ovka''', a suffix signifying an activity.
===Noun===
:'''birmovka''' ''f'', '''birmovky''' ''pl''
:'''birmovk''' ''stem''
:'''birmoviek''' ''{{genpl}}''
:{{decpat}} {{zena}}
# The ritual of the Catholic sacrament of [[confirmation]]. This word does not describe the sacrament itself (that is [[birmovanie]]), but the occasion, the ritual, the celebration, of conferring the sacrament. It is only used by Slovak Catholics, too. The Slovak Lutherans use a different word ([[konfirmácia]]).
